      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Primary hemolysis QoI validation — RH index across 5 operating points",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and relative hemolysis index (RH) were evaluated across five flow-speed operating points (3–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM) representative of CPB duty cycles. The simulation ensemble produced RH < 1 for all worst-case candidate conditions, consistent with the acceptance criterion stated in the COU. Mesh independence was confirmed at 8.2 million elements with GCI < 2.1% on NIH. Turbulence model sensitivity (SST k-ω vs. realizable k-ε) showed less than 4% variation in scalar shear stress exposure. The validation narrative references the Morrison et al. (2023) in-vitro hemolysis dataset as the basis for confidence, noting strong qualitative agreement and directionally correct rank-ordering of operating conditions. No quantitative discrepancy metric is recorded in this result node.",
      "validationMethod": "Qualitative trend comparison and rank-order agreement",
      "quantityOfInterest": "Relative Hemolysis Index (RH)",
      "acceptanceCriterion": "RH < 1.0 for all worst-case operating points",
