      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Secondary validation — scalar stress exposure comparison against LVAD benchmark dataset",
      "description": "As a supplementary credibility activity, CFD-predicted scalar shear stress exposure time (SSET) distributions were compared against the Hariharan et al. (2011) FDA benchmark dataset for the FDA generic blood pump operated under LVAD flow conditions (5 L/min, 3500 RPM continuous flow). Agreement between simulated and experimentally measured SSET cumulative distributions was within 12% at the 95th percentile, which the assessment team characterizes as good agreement. This comparison is cited as evidence that the turbulence closure and red blood cell damage model are well-calibrated. The Hariharan dataset is widely regarded as the gold-standard validation reference for blood-contacting CFD, and its use here reflects best practice in the field. The assessment narrative does not examine whether LVAD operating conditions — characterized by continuous high-speed flow against systemic vascular resistance — are representative of CPB operating conditions, which involve lower afterload, intermittent pulsatility contributions from the native heart, and a fundamentally different hemodynamic regime affecting exposure time distributions.",
